Callback_OnMenuOptionChange.description: Called whenever a menu option is changed.

Abilities_Count.description: Use this to iterate over each ability with Abilities.Get(...)

Abilities_GetAll.description: This function causes a table allocation and may be slower than using Abilities.Get()

Abilities_Contains.description: This function can be used to determine if an unknown entity is an ability type entity since only ability type entities will be contained in the Abilities list.

Heroes_Count.description: Use this number to iterate over each hero with Heroes.Get(...).

Heroes_GetAll.description: This function causes a table allocation and may be slower than using Heroes.Get()

Heroes_Contains.description: This function can be used to determine if an unknown entity is a hero type entity since only hero type entities will be contained in the Heroes list

Heroes_InRadius.description: Return: A table containing the heroes within the radius of vec

Heroes_GetLocal.description: Return: local player's hero type entity

NPCs_Count.description: Use this number to iterate over each hero with NPCs.Get(...)

NPCs_GetAll.description: This function causes a table allocation and may be slower than using NPCs.Get()

NPCs_Contains.description: This function can be used to determine if an unknown entity is a hero type entity since only hero type entities will be contained in the NPCs list

NPCs_InRadius.description: Return: A table containing the NPCs within the radius of vec

Players_Count.description: Use this number to iterate over each hero with Players.Get(...)

Players_GetAll.description: This function causes a table allocation and may be slower than using Players.Get()

Players_Contains.description: This function can be used to determine if an unknown entity is a hero type entity since only hero type entities will be contained in the Players list

Players_GetLocal.description: Return: local player's player type entity.

Trees_Count.description: Use this number to iterate over each hero with Trees.Get(...)

Trees_GetAll.description: This function causes a table allocation and may be slower than using Trees.Get()

Trees_Contains.description: This function can be used to determine if an unknown entity is a hero type entity since only hero type entities will be contained in the Trees list

Trees_InRadius.description: Return: A table containing the Trees within the radius of vec

Ability_IsAttributes.description: Return: True if ability is attributes or talents

Ability_GetLevelSpecialValueFor.description: Return: A level specific special KeyValue from this Ability's entry in npc_abilities.txt. Integers only

Ability_GetLevelSpecialValueForFloat.description: Return: A level specific special KeyValue from this Ability's entry in npc_abilities.txt. Floats only

Ability_GetCooldownTimeLeft.description: Return: A number representing the number of seconds left on the abilities cooldown

Ability_SecondsSinceLastUse.description: Return: A number representing the number of seconds since the ability was last used

Ability_GetDamage.description: Return: A number representing the damage the ability does

Ability_IsReady.description: Return: True if the ability is ready, false otherwise

Ability_IsCastable.description: Return: True if the ability is castable, false otherwise

Ability_IsPassive.description: Return: True if the ability is a passive one, false otherwise

Ability_IsChannelling.description: Return: True if the ability is currently being channeled, false otherwise

Ability_GetName.description: Return: The name of the ability, or nil if it does not have one

Ability_GetIndex.description: Return: An integer index for the ability

Ability_GetCastRange.description: Return: An integer representing the cast range of the ability

Entity_IsSameTeam.description: Return: True if the entities are on the same team

Entity_IsNPC.description: Return: True if the entity is an NPC type entity

Entity_IsHero.description: Return: True if the entity is a hero type entity

Entity_IsDormant.description: Dormant means most data for this entity is no longer being sent to the client. This is usually the case when an entity is in the Fog of War, or invisible

Entity_GetHealth.description: Return: The entity's health as an integer

Entity_GetMaxHealth.description: Return: The entity's max health as an integer

Entity_IsTurning.description: This method is the same as doing Entity.GetAngVelocity(ent):Length2d() > 0.1 but should be prefered if all you need to know is if an entity is turning

NPC_IsEntityInRange.description: This checks whether the target entity is in range of npc. It uses the hull radius of both entities. If you only want to use the hull radius of npc, consider using NPC.IsPositionInRange with hull 0

NPC_GetMoveSpeed.description: Return: A number representing the unit's move speed after modifiers

NPC_GetBaseSpeed.description: Return: A number representing the unit's move speed before modifiers

NPC_GetMoveSpeedModifier.description: Return: A number representing baseSpeed affected by modifiers

NPC_GetAbilityByIndex.description: Return: An object that can be used with the Ability table. Returns nil if ability not found

NPC_GetAbility.description: An object that can be used with the Ability table. Returns nil if ability not found

NPC_GetAttachmentByIndex.description: Needed to get the attachment location from OnProjectile

NPC_MoveTo.description: Easy wrapper function that works in place of calling Player.PrepareUnitOrders

Tree_IsActive.description: Return: True if the tree is not destroyed

NetChannel_GetLatency.description: Return: A number containing the latency in seconds

NetChannel_GetAvgLatency.description: Return: A number containing the average latency in seconds

I18n_Get.description: This table contains functions for localizing user scripts

Input_IsKeyDown.description: True if the key is down, false otherwise

Input_IsKeyDownOnce.description: True if the key was pressed once, false otherwise

Input_IsInputCaptured().description: Return: Returns true if keyboard input is being captured (eg. when chatting in the chat box or when typing in the item search box)

Log_Write.description: The string to write to the log file

Menu_IsKeyDown.description: True if the key is down, false otherwise

Menu_IsKeyDownOnce.description: True if the key was pressed once, false otherwise

Vector.description: Return: A new userdata type representing the vector

Vec_tostring.description: Return: A string representation of the Vector

Vec_add.description: Return: The result of adding vec2 to vec

Vec_sub.description: Return: The result of subtracting vec2 from vec

Vec_mul.description: Return: The result of multiplying vec by vec2

Vec_Get.description: Return: The x, y and z coordinates of vec

Vec_GetX.description: Return: The x coordinate of vec

Vec_GetY.description: Return: The Y coordinate of vec

Vec_GetZ.description: Return: The Z coordinate of vec

Vec_Length.description: The length of vec (also known as its magnitude)

Vec_LengthSqr.description: The squared length of vec which can be useful if comparing magnitudes without incurring the use of a sqrtf call (eg, is this vec shorter or longer than some other vec)

Vec_Length2D.description: The 2D length of vec (ignoring the z axis)

Vec_Length2DSqr.description: The squared 2D length of vec (see Length2D() and LengthSqr() above)

Vec_Dot.description: The dot product of vec * vec2

Vec_Dot2D.description: The 2D dot product of vec * vec2 (ignoring the z axis).

Vec_Cross.description: The cross product of vec x vec2

Vec_Project.description: The projected Vector of vec by vec2

Vec_Distance.description: The distance between vec and vec2

Vec_Scaled.description: A new Vector that is vec scaled by scalar.

Vec_ToAngle.description: Return: This vector converted to an angle

Vec_Rotated.description: A new Vector that is vec rotated by angle

Angle.description: A new userdata type representing the angle

ang_tostring.description: Return: A string representation of the angle

ang_Get.description: Return: The pitch, yaw and roll rotation values of ang

ang_GetVectors.description: The forward, right, and up vectors representing this angle

ang_GetForward.description: The forward vector of this angle

ang_GetRight.description: The right vector of this angle

ang_GetUp.description: The up vector of this angle
